                            <comment id="12879942" author="hossman" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2010 21:30:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s nothing anyone directly involved with Solr can do about this, it&apos;s a generic problem with the entire apache.org wiki installation that already has a bug filed: INFRA-2251&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879961" author="guillaumep" created="Thu, 17 Jun 2010 22:03:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing duplicate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12882910" author="tkurosaka" created="Sun, 27 Jun 2010 03:13:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is an easy work around, use the explicit link wiki.apache.org/solr/FrontPage instead of wiki.apache.org/solr.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch is attached.&lt;br/&gt;
Please reopen this bug and apply the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12883757" author="koji" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2010 01:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is an easy work around, use the explicit link wiki.apache.org/solr/FrontPage instead of wiki.apache.org/solr.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;br/&gt;
I think Kurosaka-san&apos;s fix is worth for non-english Solr users. Why don&apos;t we reopen this issue and apply the fix? Once INFRA-2251 is solved, we can revert links.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12883911" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2010 13:06:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885102" author="hossman" created="Mon, 5 Jul 2010 04:15:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW: My previous comment was in regards to the fact that we can&apos;t control/change every link to the Solr wiki on the entire Internet &amp;#8211; we can&apos;t even modify the links in the docs for past releases because it will change the artifacts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But i&apos;ve got no problem updating the site.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12886982" author="koji" created="Sat, 10 Jul 2010 02:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 962747. I&apos;d like to leave this ticket open until INFRA-2251 is solved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382503" author="ctargett" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 16:01:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems this could be closed - the linked INFRA issue is resolved, and the last comment indicates that was the reason for keeping it open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
